Return strict JSON only matching schema CardAnnotationV1:
{"worth_saving":true|false,"title":string,"summary":string,"confidence":"certain"|"likely"|"possible"|"uncertain","priority":"always_inject"|"high_recall"|"episodic_detail"|"archival","time_horizon":{"kind":"timeless"|"era_bound"|"current"|"expiring","start":string|null,"end":string|null,"as_of":string|null},"types":[string,...],"anchor_class":string|null,"tags":[string,...],"anchors":[string,...],"still_true":[string,...],"project":string|null}

You are deciding whether one user chat message contains a durable fact worth
saving to Orion's memory-cards substrate, and if so, annotating it.

Rules:
- worth_saving=false for pure chitchat / phatic exchange ("hi", "how are
  you", "thanks", "ok", acknowledgements with no new content). Do not force
  a card out of nothing -- most single turns are NOT worth saving.
- confidence reflects how directly stated (not inferred/guessed) the fact is:
  certain (explicitly stated as fact), likely (strongly implied), possible
  (plausible but uncertain), uncertain (weak signal).
- priority is an initial guess only, not a precise judgment: always_inject
  for foundational identity/anchor-level facts, high_recall for facts likely
  to matter across many future turns, episodic_detail for a one-off specific
  detail, archival for low-salience background color.
- time_horizon: if the text names a specific date or era, use
  kind="era_bound" with start (and end, if given). Otherwise default to
  kind="current" (true as of now -- an honest claim, not a false permanence
  claim). Use kind="timeless" only for facts true regardless of time.
  kind="expiring" only if the text itself signals a known future end.
- anchor_class: one of person|place|project|event|concept|relationship|
  health|preference|belief, or null if the fact is not anchor-like.
- types: short lowercase tags describing the kind of fact (e.g. "fact",
  "anchor", "preference"). tags/anchors: short lowercase keyword arrays for
  retrieval. still_true: short standalone restatements of facts still true
  after this turn (may be empty).
{%- if known_categories %}
- Known categories from Orion's real conversation history (data-driven topic
  clusters, not invented): {{ known_categories | join(", ") }}. If this fact
  clearly fits one, prefer reusing it as one of the tags -- keeps related
  memory grouped together instead of every card inventing its own wording
  for the same topic. This is a hint, not a constraint: if nothing fits,
  use your own judgment.
{%- endif %}
- Do NOT include "sensitivity" or "visibility_scope" keys in your response.
  Those are decided outside this call, never by you -- any such keys you
  emit will be ignored.

